#GitHub Repository Fetcher Script
*This script fetches a list of GitHub repositories using the GitHub API and saves the full names of the repositories to a text file.
##Description
Author: Anupa Sharma
#Key Features
*Fetches repositories from the GitHub API using a specified token for authentication.
*Paginates through results, fetching 100 repositories per page (configurable).
*Extracts and prints the full names of the repositories on the console.
*Saves the output to a text file named listofgithubrepos.txt
##Usage
*This script can be used to gather a list of GitHub repositories for analysis, research, or other similar purposes.
*Simply replace the TOKEN variable with a valid GitHub API token and run the script.
*The output will be saved to a file named listofgithubrepos.txt in the current working directory.
